    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_26708060" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/26708060" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/867010-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1211657025p2/867010.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/26708060?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/867010-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780500286968" href="/book/show/2107697.The_True_History_of_Chocolate">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer26708060" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12105498962321298794">If you like cultural anthropology and you like chocolate, then you will like this book.<br/><br/>It reads like a thesis on chocolate, but this is not a bad thing. In fact, it makes it all the more valid and interesting. Included are several pages of references so you, too, can continue your knowledge of this wonderful plant product.<br/><br/>I would say this book is more geared for those scientifically inclined, but the history of chocolate&apos;s spread throughout the world is still a good read for anyone.</span>
  <span id="freeText12105498962321298794" style="display:none">If you like cultural anthropology and you like chocolate, then you will like this book.<br /><br />It reads like a thesis on chocolate, but this is not a bad thing. In fact, it makes it all the more valid and interesting. Included are several pages of references so you, too, can continue your knowledge of this wonderful plant product.<br /><br />I would say this book is more geared for those scientifically inclined, but the history of chocolate's spread throughout the world is still a good read for anyone.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12105498962321298794" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


