    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer149401150" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11839010870587112694">An excellent read that covers &quot;the bean&quot; from it&apos;s original use by mesoamericans to today&apos;s high end and fair trade producers. This book gives a fascinating look at how cocoa has been used and viewed through out history. Originally viewed as a delicacy for the affluent, them viewed as a medical tool and finally as an everyman&apos;s treat. I would have liked a little more on the business of chocolate and the science of how a lowly not particularly good tasting bean (we all tried tasting that baking c</span>
  <span id="freeText11839010870587112694" style="display:none">An excellent read that covers "the bean" from it's original use by mesoamericans to today's high end and fair trade producers. This book gives a fascinating look at how cocoa has been used and viewed through out history. Originally viewed as a delicacy for the affluent, them viewed as a medical tool and finally as an everyman's treat. I would have liked a little more on the business of chocolate and the science of how a lowly not particularly good tasting bean (we all tried tasting that baking chocolate in moms pantry) grew into a beloved, some might argue staple. Perhaps that can be part of the third edition. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11839010870587112694" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


